ne 106:     应用存入数据到Preferences实例后，可以使用flush()方法实现数据持久化。示例代码如下所示：\r\n\n  Line 112:     dataPreferences.getOrThrow().flush()\r\n\n  Line 139:     dataPreferences.getOrThrow().on(PreferencesEvent.PreferencesChange, preferenceCallback)\r\n\n  Line 141:     dataPreferences.getOrThrow().put(\"startup\", PreferencesValueType.StringData(\"manual\"))\r\n\n  Line 143:     dataPreferences.getOrThrow().flush()\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\\通过用户首选项实现数据持久化\\开发步骤\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: 本目录包含仓颉语言在HarmonyOS应用开发中的轻量级数据存储教程，重点讲解Preferences API的使用。内容涵盖了从模块导入、实例获取、数据读写与删除、持久化操作到数据变更监听的完整流程，以及如何彻底移除Preferences实例及其文件。文档旨在帮助具备基础仓颉语言能力的开发者快速掌握本地数据持久化技术，适用于需要管理用户偏好设置或轻量级数据的场景。关键词：Preferences、数据持久化、仓颉、API教程。\r\n\n  Line 7: - 你想学习Preferences的基础开发流程（读写、保存、监听）？ → 开发步骤_1.md\r\n\n  Line 8: - 你想彻底删除Preferences实例及其相关文件？ → 开发步骤_2.md\r\n\n  Line 13: 本文档是一份针对仓颉语言的轻量级数据存储开发教程，旨在指导开发者使用Preferences API进行本地数据管理。内容涵盖模块导入、获取实例、数据写入与读取、数据删除、持久化操作、数据变更订阅以及文件删除等八个主要步骤。重点介绍了put、get、delete、flush等核心方法的使用，以及通过自定义Callback实现数据变更监听的机制。适用于具备基础仓颉语言和HarmonyOS应用开发能力的开发者，帮助其快速掌握轻量级数据持久化技术。关键词：Preferences、数据持久化、仓颉、API教程。\r\n\n  Line 16: 本文档主要介绍如何使用deletePreferences方法从内存及持久化存储中彻底移除指定的Preferences实例及其相关文件。涵盖了方法的功能描述、调用后的注意事项以及Cangjie语言的示例代码。关键信息包括：该方法会同时删除备份和损坏文件；调用后严禁继续使用该实例以免数据不一致；删除操作不可逆。面向使用Cangjie语言进行应用开发的程序员，适用于需要清理或重置用户偏好数据的场景。\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\\通过用户首选项实现数据持久化\\开发步骤\\.abstract.md:\n  Line 1: 本目录包含仓颉语言在HarmonyOS应用开发中的轻量级数据存储教程，重点讲解Preferences API的使用。内容涵盖了从模块导入、实例获取、数据读写与删除、持久化操作到数据变更监听的完整流程，以及如何彻底移除Preferences实例及其文件。文档旨在帮助具备基础仓颉语言能力的开发者快速掌握本地数据持久化技术，适用于需要管理用户偏好设置或轻量级数据的场景。关键词：Preferences、数据持久化、仓颉、API教程。\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\\通过用户首选项实现数据持久化\\.overview.md:\n  Line 13: 本文档旨在介绍如何利用用户首选项实现轻量级数据的持久化存储。主要涵盖场景介绍、运作机制、约束限制及核心接口说明。关键信息指出该机制采用Key-Value键值型处理，数据缓存在内存中，需通过flush接口持久化。文档详细说明了数据类型限制、并发安全风险及getPreferences、put、flush等API的使用规范。适用于需要保存用户个性化设置的应用开发者，建议具备仓颉开发基础。\r\n\n  Line 16: 本目录包含仓颉语言在HarmonyOS应用开发中的轻量级数据存储教程，重点讲解Preferences API的使用。内容涵盖了从模块导入、实例获取、数据读写与删除、持久化操作到数据变更监听的完整流程，以及如何彻底移除Preferences实例及其文件。文档旨在帮助具备基础仓颉语言能力的开发者快速掌握本地数据持久化技术，适用于需要管理用户偏好设置或轻量级数据的场景。关键词：Preferences、数据持久化、仓颉、API教程。\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\\.overview.md:\n  Line 1: # cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\r\n\n  Line 3: This directory serves as a comprehensive technical resource for implementing data persistence within HarmonyOS applications, specifically focusing on the \"User Preferences\" module. It is designed to help developers manage lightweight data efficiently using a Key-Value storage model, which is optimal for storing user settings and configuration data without the overhead of a full database. The documentation covers essential topics such as the core API usage standards, supported data types, and potential concurrency safety risks that developers must mitigate to ensure application stability. Furthermore, it provides a specialized tutorial utilizing the Cangjie programming language, guiding users through data reading, writing, and change monitoring. This guide is ideal for developers looking to implement user personalization features who have a foundational understanding of Cangjie.\r\n\n  Line 16: This subdirectory provides an in-depth introduction to utilizing user preferences for achieving lightweight data persistence in HarmonyOS applications. The primary focus is on the Key-Value storage mechanism, a robust solution that allows for the efficient storage and retrieval of simple data types. The content thoroughly details the core API usage specifications, ensuring developers understand the correct methods for interacting with the storage layer. It also addresses critical technical constraints, including specific data type limitations and concurrency safety risks, which are vital for preventing data corruption in multi-threaded environments.\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\\.abstract.md:\n  Line 1: This directory serves as a comprehensive technical resource for implementing data persistence within HarmonyOS applications, specifically focusing on the \"User Preferences\" module. It is designed to help developers manage lightweight data efficiently us...\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-data-mgmt-overview\\cj-data-mgmt-overview.md:\n  Line 28: - 用户首选项（Preferences）：提供了轻量级配置数据的持久化能力，并支持订阅数据变化的通知能力。不支持分布式同步，常用于保存应用配置信息、用户偏好设置等。\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\cj-app-data-persistence-overview\\cj-app-data-persistence-overview.md:\n  Line 15: - **用户首选项（Preferences）：** 通常用于保存应用的配置信息。数据通过文本的形式保存在设备中，应用使用过程中会将文本中的数据全量加载到内存中，所以访问速度快、效率高，但不适合需要存储大量数据的场景。\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\README_zh\\README_zh.md:\n  Line 8:   - [通过用户首选项实现数据持久化](cj-data-persistence-by-preferences.md)（Beta特性）\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: This directory serves as a comprehensive technical resource for the ArkData module on the OpenHarmony platform. It covers the full spectrum of data management, including standardized data definitions (UTD), various persistence mechanisms (Preferences, KV-Store, RelationalStore), cross-device synchronization, and data security (encryption, backup, access control). Designed for application developers, it provides guidance on selecting the right storage solutions, implementing distributed data consistency, and ensuring data reliability. Whether dealing with lightweight configuration or complex relational data, this documentation addresses the needs of developers building robust, secure, and high-performance applications.\r\n\n  Line 12:     *   Lightweight configuration → [8] cj-data-persistence-by-preferences\r\n\n  Line 29: This directory is the Chinese navigation index for the ArkData module, aiming to provide a comprehensive entry point for data management functionality documentation for application developers. The documentation covers standardized data definitions (UTD), various data persistence schemes (Preferences, Key-Value databases, Relational databases), cross-device data synchronization for the same application, and data reliability and security (backup and recovery, encryption, access control). All features are currently Beta, suitable for developers requiring data storage, synchronization, and security management to consult as a directory for ArkData-related development guides.\r\n\n  Line 35: This directory focuses on application data persistence mechanisms under the OpenHarmony standard system, aiming to guide developers in persisting in-memory data to the device. Content covers three core data storage forms: User Preferences for lightweight configuration, Key-Value Database (KV-Store) for distributed scenarios and simple business data, and RelationalStore supporting complex queries and custom SQL. By comparing the characteristics and applicable scenarios of each form, the document helps developers make the best choice based on specific business needs. This is a conceptual guide for OpenHarmony application developers.\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\Guide\\database\\.abstract.md:\n  Line 1: This directory serves as a comprehensive technical resource for the ArkData module on the OpenHarmony platform. It covers t