{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782299024864,"sessionID":"ses_106b70cc2ffeQ7z094Vd8ASez1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_hzU0F6EDnbe2b7ESwjaW3rNp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"path":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search","pattern":"resource|string resources|Resource|Color","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 6434 matches (showing first 100)\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\tools\\cmd-tools\\cjprof_manual\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: This directory serves as the comprehensive technical manual for `cjprof`, the dedicated performance analysis tool designed specifically for the Cangjie programming language. It provides essential guidance for developers and DevOps engineers who are focused on optimizing application performance and resolving complex operational issues within a Linux environment. The documentation thoroughly covers critical profiling capabilities, such as CPU hotspot function sampling to detect high-load execution paths, exporting granular performance data, and generating visual statistical reports and flame graphs to facilitate easier analysis. Additionally, it addresses memory integrity by detailing the procedures for exporting and analyzing heap memory, which is crucial for identifying and rectifying memory leaks. By leveraging the methodologies outlined in this manual, users can effectively diagnose system bottlenecks, enhance resource utilization, and ensure the stability of their Cangjie-based software solutions.\r\n\n  Line 18: This directory introduces `cjprof`, the official performance analysis tool for the Cangjie language, aimed at helping developers perform application performance tuning and troubleshooting. The content covers a wide range of functionalities, starting with CPU hotspot function sampling, which allows users to pinpoint specific functions that are consuming excessive processing power. It also provides detailed instructions on exporting performance data and creating statistical reports and flame graphs, which are vital for visualizing system behavior and identifying optimization opportunities. Furthermore, the guide includes sections on heap memory export and analysis, offering the necessary techniques to detect and resolve memory leaks. Core keywords associated with this documentation include cjprof, performance analysis, CPU sampling, and memory leak troubleshooting. This resource is specifically intended for developers and operations personnel who need to conduct performance optimization for Cangjie applications in a Linux environment.\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\tools\\cmd-tools\\cjpm_manual\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: This directory serves as the comprehensive manual for the Cangjie Programming Language's official project management tool, CJPM. It covers the entire software development lifecycle, including project initialization, building, testing, and installation or uninstallation. The documentation provides detailed insights into command-line usage, configuration specifications, build scripts, and dependency management. Key topics include CJPM, package management, build configuration, and dependency resolution. This resource is designed for Cangjie developers who want to efficiently organize their code, automate build processes, and resolve common development issues.\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\tools\\cmd-tools\\cjlint_manual\\.abstract.md:\n  Line 1: This directory serves as the comprehensive documentation repository for CJLint, the dedicated static analysis tool designed for the Cangjie programming language. It provides essential resources for developers to identify code vulnerabilities, enforce co...\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\tools\\cmd-tools\\cjlint_manual\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: This directory serves as the comprehensive documentation repository for CJLint, the dedicated static analysis tool designed for the Cangjie programming language. It provides essential resources for developers to identify code vulnerabilities, enforce coding standards, and manage warnings effectively. The documentation covers command-line usage, configuration options for suppressing alerts at various levels, and detailed specifications regarding lock management and syntax restrictions. It is intended for all Cangjie language developers seeking to improve code quality, ensure security, and maintain consistency across their projects through automated static checking. Whether you are integrating the tool into a CI/CD pipeline or using it locally for code review, this manual offers the necessary guidance to optimize your development workflow and ensure robust code delivery.\r\n\n  Line 17: Additionally, the documentation explains how to configure warning suppression at both the file level and the rule level, offering developers granular control over which alerts to ignore. Beyond basic usage, it details the tool's technical specifications, such as lock management rules and settings to disable specific syntax features. These documents are designed to assist developers in proactively discovering code vulnerabilities and standardizing code style, making them a vital resource for all Cangjie language developers.\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\tools\\cmd-tools\\cjdb_manual\\.overview.md:\n  Line 3: This directory serves as the comprehensive manual for `cjdb`, the dedicated command-line debugging tool for the Cangjie programming language. It provides essential resources and documentation for developers aiming to debug executables efficiently across Windows, Linux, and macOS operating systems. Built upon the robust LLDB framework, the manual covers a wide range of topics including tool introduction, executable debugging guides, frequently asked questions, and detailed command references. Key fu