ments designed to facilitate the integration of single-line text input fields. The scope of the content extends from basic component initialization to complex controller management and interaction event handling. By offering detailed insights into attribute configuration, this documentation enables developers to achieve precise control over input behavior and visual styling. Whether you are building a simple search bar or a complex data entry form, this resource provides the necessary technical specifications. It is an essential guide for software engineers and UI developers aiming to build responsive and user-friendly text entry interfaces in their HarmonyOS applications.\r\n\n  Line 8: *   Get started with the TextInput component basics and API structure → `TextInput/`\r\n\n  Line 9: *   Learn how to initialize and construct the component in Cangjie → `TextInput/`\r\n\n  Line 10: *   Manage controllers and handle user interaction events effectively → `TextInput/`\r\n\n  Line 11: *   Configure attributes for custom styling and input behavior → `TextInput/`\r\n\n  Line 15: ### TextInput/\r\n\n  Line 16: This directory contains API reference documentation for the TextInput component within the ArkUI framework, designed specifically for HarmonyOS applications developed using the Cangjie language. The documentation provides a structured approach to implementing single-line text input functionality, covering the entire lifecycle of the component.\r\n\n  Line 18: Key areas covered include component initialization construction, which guides developers through the necessary steps to instantiate the text input field correctly using Cangjie syntax. It also details controller management, allowing for advanced manipulation of the input state, such as focus control and cursor positioning. Furthermore, the section on interaction event handling explains how to respond to user actions effectively, capturing inputs like text changes and submission events. The comprehensive attribute configuration documentation enables developers to fine-tune input behavior and styles, ensuring the component fits seamlessly into the application's design. With core keywords such as ArkUI, TextInput, Cangjie language, API reference, event handling, and component attributes, these documents are suitable for developers seeking to implement robust text entry solutions with granular control over the user interface.\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\API\\arkui-cj\\cj-text-input-search\\Search\\组件属性.md:\n  Line 101: > - 设置CopyOptions.None时，当前Search中的文字无法被复制、剪切、翻译和帮写，仅支持粘贴。\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\API\\arkui-cj\\cj-text-input-search\\Search\\基础类型定义_2more_0f662c95.md:\n  Line 3: ### class SearchController\r\n\n  Line 6: public class SearchController <: TextContentControllerBase {\r\n\n  Line 11: **功能：** Search组件的控制器。\r\n\n  Line 27: **功能：** 创建SearchController类型的对象。\r\n\n  Line 66:     let controller = SearchController()\r\n\n  Line 71:           Search(value: \"\", placeholder: \"Type to search\", controller: controller)\r\n\n  Line 72:             //设置搜索框末尾搜索按钮文本内容为\"SearchBtn\"\r\n\n  Line 73:             .searchButton(\"SearchBtn\")\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\API\\arkui-cj\\cj-text-input-search\\Search\\Search_5more_07cedc0c.md:\n  Line 1: # Search\r\n\n  Line 23: ### init(?ResourceStr, ?ResourceStr, Option\\<AppResource>, Option\\<SearchController>)\r\n\n  Line 30:     controller!: Option<SearchController> = None\r\n\n  Line 34: **功能：** 创建Search组件。\r\n\n  Line 47: |controller|Option\\<[SearchController](#class-searchcontroller)>|否|None|**命名参数。** Search组件控制器。|\r\n\n\nD:\\workspace\\Foodike\\.agents\\skills\\cangjie-harmonyos-doc-search\\harmonyos-6.1-8k\\API\\arkui-cj\\cj-text-input-search\\Search\\.overview.md:\n  Line 1: # Search\r\n\n  Line 3: 本目录包含基于仓颉语言的ArkUI框架Search